== a fifo is -p, a plain file is not:
fifo-yes
plain-not-fifo
== /dev/null is a character device, a plain file is not:
char-yes
plain-not-char
== a plain file is neither a block device nor a socket:
blk-no
sock-no
== -O reports the file is owned by the effective user:
owned
== -o reads the real state of a shell option:
pipefail-on
pipefail-off
emacs-on
unknown-off
== the [ ] builtin agrees with [[ ]] on the file-type primaries:
bracket-fifo-yes
bracket-setuid-no
bracket-owned
